Features
--------
- Computes two-loop QCD amplitudes in the leading-color approximation
- Supports massless bottom quarks with a massive Higgs
- Implemented in C++ for efficiency and easy integration into Monte Carlo frameworks

Dependencies
------------
- PentagonFunctions (for evaluation of pentagon integrals)
- qd-library (for high-precision arithmetic)

Installation
------------
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone <repository_url>
   cd pphbb_twoloop

2. Make sure PentagonFunctions and qd-library are installed and accessible.

3. Build the library using your preferred build system (Make or CMake).

Usage
-----
Compilation of the library performed externally by the makefile of
the POWHEG LC-twoloop interface in ../interface-LC

